<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-197-170  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 197 170.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  March 1990 v7 n3 p121(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Observing an Oracle database. (Oracle Corp.'s Oracle Graphicscomputer graphics software)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Littman, Dan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Oracle Corp is developing Oracle Graphics, software thatestablishes links to an SQL database and displays data in livecharts and graphs.andP;  Oracle Graphics can create 51 standard graphsin either column, line, mixed column and line, double-y, scatterplot, pie, high-low or tables of columnar data.andP;  Oracle Graphics'automatically updates its graphs and animated pictures to reflectchanges in the data base.andP;  Dynamic object linking is used tocreate animated pictures.andP;  The user must write SQL statements inorder to design a graphing application.andP;  Importing illustrationscan be accomplished with PICT, EPS and other formats; OracleGraphics also features its own tool palette.andP;  The application iscompatible with all Oracle platforms.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Oracle Corp. (product development).andO;Ticker:    ORCL.andO;Product:   Oracle Graphics (Computer graphics software) (productdevelopment).andO;Topic:     Computer graphicsGraphics SoftwareProduct DevelopmentData ProcessingAnimation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>